properties.areaDesc: Wind River Mountains West; Upper Green River Basin Foothills
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 16 at 3:56AM MST until February 16 at 11:00PM MST by NWS Riverton WY
properties.description:
...Winter Storm for Western Wyoming through this Evening...

.A storm system will bring significant snow across much of
western Wyoming today through this evening.

* WHAT and WHERE...Periods of snow, moderate at times, across the
Upper Green River Basin Foothills, and the western slopes of the
Wind River Mountains. New snowfall through tonight will range
from 6 to 10 inches in the mountains. Additional snowfall of 2
to 4 inches will occur around Pinedale through this evening with
4 to 5 inches around Bondurant. Snowfall around South Pass will
range from 2 to 3 inches along with a gusty wind.

* WHEN...Until 11 PM Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult at times. Some
blowing snow could significantly reduce visibility including
South Pass.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Plan for adverse winter weather if
recreating this weekend.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 PM MST THIS EVENING
